        <updateDate>2022-06-01T15:02:17Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><strong>Mandatory Minimum Reform Act of 2020</strong></p> <p>This bill eliminates most mandatory minimum prison terms for drug offenses involving the import, export, manufacture, distribution, or possession with intent to distribute a controlled substance.</p> <p>Additionally, it eliminates mandatory minimum prison terms for the following drug offenses: </p> <ul> <li>simple possession, </li> <li> distribution to an individual under age 21 by an individual at least age 18, </li> <li>distribution or manufacture in a school zone, and </li> <li>use of an individual under age 18 to distribute. </li> </ul> <p>Finally, the bill requires prior written approval of the Attorney General to prosecute a defendant for certain drug offenses that involve low-level drug quantities (e.g., less than one kilogram of heroin or less than 500 grams of cocaine-based substances).</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
